owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: The aim of the ontology is to represent the knowledge related to drones' semantic trajectories (flights, missions, recordings). Reuses datAcron ontology.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: onto4drone
owl:Ontology.owl:versionInfo:
version 1.0.1
This version includes two extra data properties whose domain is the class DroneCarryingEquipment, three extra data properties whose domain is the class Record, one data properties whose domain is the class EntityOfInterest and two data properties whose domain is the class RegionOfInterest. Regarding the object properties two inverse object properties (has occured event" and "is produced by") and one more object property ("has interest") have been added.
Furthremore, axioms have been added to the classes Record, Recording Position, and Constant Recording Position.
Additionally, the class EntityOfInterest has been moved under the DUL general class Entity, while the data property "has time" has been removed as well.
Finally some changes/additions which have been conducted to the domains and/or ranges of the data properties hasAltittude, TimeEnd, TimeStart, and has interval date have been removed as well.
Regarding individuals, there have been added all the individuals presented in the example of the knowledge graph designed by the group (https://arrows.app/#/googledrive/ids=1f-NEXdFHa0bSXGaBI6MoCpLdOyLtFXP2).

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the equipment carried by a drone
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: carries equipment

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the trajectory that the segments is part of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: encloses

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the drone that participates in an event.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has drone participant

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Correlates an entity of interest with the type of interest that it presents.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has interest

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the moving object that forms the trajectory.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has trajectory

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines the moving object that the trajectory is referring to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: trajectory refers to

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies flightes included in a misson
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: includes flight

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the record produced by a recornding event
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: produces

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the records an entity has been recorded in
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is recorded in

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the entity that is beeing recorded in a recording event
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: records

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines the trajectories clusetered in a TrajectorCluster
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: clusters

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines the record from which a processed record originates
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: originates from

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Any type of unmanned vehicle, aerial or marine (surface or underwater).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The equipment carried by the drone for different purposes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone Carrying Equipment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The aerial recording (process) of a region of interest, a movable or immovable object of interest, a moving or still object of interest, an event of interest.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Recording Event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An aircraft without any human pilot, crew or passengers on board. The flight of the drone can be operated either remotely by a human or by a software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: UAV drone

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The entity of interest of any kind (object, event, living organism), that the recording activity aims to record.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Entity of Interest

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The mission of the drone flight. It may comprise more than one flight.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A set of drones flying in formation and collaboration to accomplish a mission
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Swarm of drones

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The result of the recording process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Record

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A record which has been processed by experts using specialised software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Processed Record

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The specific region that the recording activity aims to record. The region of interest may be a forest, an archaeological space, a town etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Region of Interest

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The spatiotemporal position on which recording -constantly- occurs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Constant Recording Position

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The spatiotemporal position on which recording -instantly- occurs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Recording Position

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The device used for laser scanning.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone Laser Scanner

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The devices used for the recording, and carried by the drone.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone Recording Equipment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The equipment used for military purposes, carried by the drone
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone Military Equipment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The device used for photography.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone Photographic Camera

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The device used for video recording.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drone Video Camera

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The specific event that the recording activity aims to record. This event may be a natural phenomenon, the movement of an individual etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Event of Interest

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: To model military-related events (of drones carrying guns)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GunShooting

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A laser scanner recording event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Laser Scanning Event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A set of data points in space which represent a 3D shape or object captured by a laser scanner.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Point Cloud

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The specific physical object that the recording activity aims to record. The object of interest may be a tree, a monument, a person etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Object of Interest

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A photograph that captures horizontally elongated fields of view.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Panoramic Photograph

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A picture made using a photographic camera.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Photograph

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A photographic camera recording event which results in panoramic photos.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Panoramic Shooting Event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A photographic camera recording event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Photo Shooting Event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The specific spatial point that the recording activity aims to record. The point of interest may be literally one geometric point or an central point of a wider entity of interest.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Point of Interest

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The process of recording which takes place in certain spatiotemporal positions regarding the trajectory of the flying drone.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Recording Segment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of flying entities which aggregate together and move en masse in the same direction, while they may have the same or close departure and starting point. Perhaps the flying entities have a common or similar mission.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Swarm

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A marine vehicle without any human pilot, crew or passengers on board. The trip of the drone can be operated either remotely by a human or by a software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: UMV drone

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A record of moving visual images captured by a video camera.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Video

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A video camera recording event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Video Recording Event
